    "analysis": "Last attempt to find traces referencing Mysql02 returned no visible results (execution produced None). We still need to know whether Mysql02 appears in traces (as a called DB service or service with traces) to decide if it is the downstream faulty service in call chains. Traces are necessary to confirm causal direction between DB anomalies and service-level latency spikes. Because the previous trace-search cell likely executed but did not print results, we should re-run an explicit, bounded trace search and request a compact printed table so we can see whether any traces mention Mysql02 and any windowed anomalies tied to it. This is required before finalizing the root cause.",
